            <li class="list-group-item">You should never put high toxic waste into your bin, poured down the drain, or left out on the nature strip during hard rubbish collections. Victoria Government has event “Detox Your Home” which help common household drop off unwanted chemicals to trained specialist chemists who are licensed to accept toxic chemicals. Alost 40 pop-up events are hosted around Victoria each year in partnership with local councils. Keep in mind, household chemicals cannot be accepted at waste transfer stations due to the risk of fire or explosion when these items are combined or stored in large volumes. </li>
